Preheat your oven to 200°C. Pour the cold @Water{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @Salt{1/4%tsp}, cover with the lid and bring to the boil on medium-high heat. Once boiling, turn the heat down to its lowest setting. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Halve the @Red Chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed then finely chop. Drain the juice from the @Pineapple Rings{1} into a #small bowl{}. Add the @Soy Sauce{25%ml}, @Miso Paste{15%g} and @Honey{15%g} to the bowl with the juice, stir to combine. Heat a #large frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @Desiccated Coconut{25%g} and cook, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch the coconut like a hawk as it can burn easily.

Remove the coconut from the pan and set aside. In the same pan on high heat (no oil), add the pineapple slices and cook until nicely charred, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn only every couple of minutes - this will result in the pineapple picking up some colour.

Once the pineapple is cooked, chop it into 1 cm chunks and pop it into a #bowl{} with the @Rice Vinegar{15%ml}, a pinch of @Salt{pinch}, the chilli and the @Sugar{1%tsp}. Stir together and keep to one side.

> Add less chilli if you don't like too much heat.

Pop the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @Oil{}, season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Roast on the top shelf of the oven until tender and crispy, ~{10-12%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Pop the #frying pan{} back onto medium-high heat with a drizzle of @Oil{}. Season the @Sea Bream Fillets{2} with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Once hot, carefully place your sea bream in the pan, skin-side down. Cook for ~{3-4%minutes} before turning over and cooking for ~{2-3%minutes} on the other side.

> TIP: To get crispy skin on the fish, don't move it around when it's cooking skin-side down.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque all the way through.

Once the fish is cooked, transfer it to a #plate{}. Pop the pan back on medium-high heat. Add the soy-miso mixture to the pan and bring to the boil. Allow it to bubble and thicken slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, stir in the toasted coconut and half the @Black Sesame Seeds{5%g}. Divide the rice between your plates and top with the crispy bream and soy miso drizzle. Share the salsa and Tenderstem® between the plates. Sprinkle over the remaining black sesame seeds. Enjoy!